<td>&nbsp;</td><td bgcolor='#bcb09e'><img src='themes/LotusCult/images/pixel.gif' width='1' height='1' border='0' alt=''></td><td bgcolor='#ffffff'><img src='themes/LotusCult/images/pixel.gif' width='5' height='1' border='0' alt=''></td><td width='100%' valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF'><table cellpadding='15' cellspacing='0' border='0' width='100%'>
<tr><td bgcolor='#ffffff'>
<table width="100%" border="0"><tr><td valign="top" width="85%">
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#cfcfbb"><tr><td>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="8" bgcolor="#ffffff"><tr><td>
<table border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="3" width="100%"><tr><td class="article-table" align="left"><a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=36&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">*PoP*</a></td><td class="article-table" align="right">Posted by: Anonymous&nbsp;</td></tr></table><table border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="3" width="100%"><tr><td class="article-table" align="left"><span class="article-table-topic"><a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=&amp;topic=3"><img src="images/topics/everquest.gif" border="0" Alt="Everquest" align="left" hspace="5" vspace="5"></a></span><span class="article-table-text">We spent most of the day exploring the new planes, more specifically: Plane of Nightmare. First thing that must be said is a big kudos to the verant graphic designers.. after hours on end of killing either a four armed akhevan or a robed shade, it was amazing to see some of the new models they've put in. Overall the expansion looks very smooth. The raid window is particularly nice (it's about time too), hopefully they will get around to making it a little more intuitive to use soon. Anyway - back to our exploring in PoN. First impression of the zone was that it was much like PoGrowth, just without all the warm fuzzy woodland creatures. We started off by killing some named Treant near the zone in, who proved to be far easier than we had expected and dropped pretty crappy loot in line with the difficulty. After that we decided to roam around a bit, and - after several trains due to people running blindly ahead - managed to find a couple of large, evil looking undead knight type things:<br /><br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/231002/ponguards.jpg" WIDTH="500" HEIGHT="203" ALT="" BORDER="2"></DIV><br /><br />
They died easily, and didn't drop anything of note, so we pressed on in search of something more challenging to kill. We came across a city of undead, and, after wandering around for a bit killing random mobs, we found our way up to a boss - Mujaki the Devourer:<br /><br />
<br /><br />
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=4 ALIGN="center"><TR><TD VALIGN="middle"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/231002/mujaki1.jpg" WIDTH="340" HEIGHT="427" ALT="" BORDER="2"></TD><TD VALIGN="middle"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/231002/mujaki2.jpg" WIDTH="600" HEIGHT="333" ALT="" BORDER="2"></TD></TR></TABLE><br /><br />
Pretty cool looking boss. Pity he wasn't really as hard as his evil looks might imply, although the encounter was certainly interesting. <br /><br />
<br /><br />
I don't have loot shots from the above attempt, because shortly after he died the entire plane decided to crash. Some of the guild did manage to get back up there for another attempt once the plane had been revived, with the following results:<br /><br />
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=4 ALIGN="center"><TR><TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/itempics/recurvedwormwoodbow.jpg" WIDTH="451" HEIGHT="240" ALT="" BORDER="0"><BR>Grats Darkil!</TD><TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/itempics/cloakofdaggers.jpg" WIDTH="451" HEIGHT="240" ALT="" BORDER="0"><BR>Grats Wango!</TD></TR></TABLE><br /><br />
<br /><br />
We didn't find time to try any other stuff, however the general consensus seems to be that PoP is pretty damn cool overall. We still have quite a few members missing the expansion, so once they're all PoP equipped we will likely start attempting some of the harder content out there.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
<HR SIZE=1><br /><br />
<B>In other news..</B><br /><br />
Knocked off Aten again: <A HREF="#" onClick="window.open('http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/lootimg.php?itemname=Mask of Judgement&path=itempics&img=maskofjudgement.jpg','loot','height=280,width=470,resizable'); return false">Mask of Judgement</A> - Redlance (Oops!), <A HREF="#" onClick="window.open('http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/lootimg.php?itemname=Great Shadow Platemail&path=itempics&img=greatshadowplatemail.jpg','loot','height=280,width=470,resizable'); return false">Great Shadow Platemail</A> - Obfob, <A HREF="#" onClick="window.open('http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/lootimg.php?itemname=Tome of Secrets&path=itempics&img=tomeofsecrets.jpg','loot','height=280,width=470,resizable'); return false">Tome of Secrets</A> - Gladorr, <A HREF="#" onClick="window.open('http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/lootimg.php?itemname=Talisman of Vah Kerrath&path=itempics&img=talismanofvahkerrath.jpg','loot','height=280,width=470,resizable'); return false">Talisman of Vah Kerrath</A> - Grongl, Ancient: Lullaby of Shadow - Poplypop. Also cleared out a bunch of the other VT bosses on the way to her, not entirely sure what dropped or who got it since I was apparently too lazy to make note of it at the time. If you're really interested in the sort of stuff that drops there, check out the past updates since most of the item stats are listed there.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
<B>Post-Nerf Emperor Ssraeshza Dominated!</B><br /><br />
You heard it here first! (well probably not actually) The post-modrod-nerf Emperor was taken down for the first time on Quellious by Lotus Cult recently, with far lower than normal attendance and a distinct lack of healing power. Everyone present stepped up a notch and we managed to lay the smack down on the boss of Ssra once again, in what must be said is a far more enjoyable fight. He put out a nice haul of loot for us yet again, Expediter scored an <A HREF="#" onClick="window.open('http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/lootimg.php?itemname=Acrylia Handled Broadsword&path=itempics&img=acryliahandledbroadsword.jpg','loot','height=280,width=470,resizable'); return false">Acrylia Handled Broadsword</A> (arguably the most valuable no-drop 1hs on the Emperor's loot table!), Darkil picked up a <A HREF="#" onClick="window.open('http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/lootimg.php?itemname=Shield of Mental Fortitude&path=itempics&img=shieldofmentalfortitude.jpg','loot','height=280,width=470,resizable'); return false">Shield of Mental Fortitude</A>, while Trabious slipped into a pair of <A HREF="#" onClick="window.open('http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/lootimg.php?itemname=Envenomed Moccasins&path=itempics&img=envenomedmoccasins.jpg','loot','height=280,width=470,resizable'); return false">Envenomed Moccasins</A> (yes the haste is indeed 41% as can be verified <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_item_info.html?num=30569">here</A>).<br /><br />
<br /><br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/231002/emp.jpg" WIDTH="592" HEIGHT="207" ALT="" BORDER="2"></DIV><br /><br />
<br /><br />
<B>Quotes-n-stuff:</B><br /><br />
<br /><br />
I didn't think this really warranted it's own section, but the corpse shot was just too cool. We paid a visit to King Tormax after one of the many PoP-induced patches; it's always fun to try out our new mob positioning skills on some older content. Loot of note: King T's Head - Terrai, ST key - Escad.<br /><br />
<br /><br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/231002/ktcorpse.jpg" WIDTH="400" HEIGHT="174" ALT="" BORDER="0"><BR>Yes.. that's his big toe sticking out of the wall.</DIV><br /><br />
<br /><br />
<IMG SRC="http://www.lotuscult.com/~tase/updates/231002/poplyrod.jpg" WIDTH="451" HEIGHT="31" ALT="" BORDER="0"><br /><br />
